    <h1>JonaStars ID System</h1>
    <p>Hey there! Welcome to the ID system documentation. This guide explains how our unique ID generation works and what makes a valid ID in our system.</p>

    <h2>Quick Start</h2>
    <div class="example-box">
        Allowed characters:
        • Letters: P, L, Q, G, R, J, C, U, V
        • Numbers: 0, 2, 8, 9
    </div>

    <h2>ID Structure & Rules</h2>
    <h3>Basic Rules:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Minimum length: 3 characters</li>
        <li>IDs get longer as we run out of shorter combinations</li>
        <li>Each ID must be unique in the system</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Length Progression System</h2>
    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>Stage</th>
            <th>Length</th>
            <th>Real Examples</th>
            <th>Notes</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Starting Point</td>
            <td>3 chars</td>
            <td>P02, L28, Q90</td>
            <td>Most common format for new users</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Second Wave</td>
            <td>4 chars</td>
            <td>PL02, QR28, GJ90</td>
            <td>Used when 3-char IDs run low</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Extended</td>
            <td>5+ chars</td>
            <td>PLQ02, GRJ28, CUV90</td>
            <td>For high-volume systems</td>
        </tr>
    </table>

    <h2>Real-world Examples</h2>
    <div class="example-box">
    Good IDs:
    • P02  (basic)
    • LQ28 (mixed)
    • GRJ90 (extended)
    • PLQV028 (complex)
    
    Bad IDs:
    • A1 (wrong chars + too short)
    • PPP (no numbers)
    • 123 (invalid numbers)
    </div>

    <h2>Common Questions</h2>
    <div class="note">
        <strong>Q: Why these specific characters?</strong><br>
        These characters were chosen for clarity and minimal confusion. For example, we skip similar-looking characters like O and 0.
    </div>

    <h2>Technical Implementation Tips</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Store IDs in uppercase (P02 instead of p02)</li>
        <li>No spaces allowed in IDs</li>
        <li>Quick validation regex: <code>/^[PLQGRJCUV][PLQGRJCUV0289]+$/</code></li>
        <li>Minimum total length: 3 characters</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>ID Validation Checklist</h2>
    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>Check</th>
            <th>Example</th>
            <th>Result</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Only allowed characters?</td>
            <td>P02 vs A1B</td>
            <td>✓ vs ✗</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Minimum length (3)?</td>
            <td>P02 vs P2</td>
            <td>✓ vs ✗</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>At least one letter?</td>
            <td>P02 vs 028</td>
            <td>✓ vs ✗</td>
        </tr>
    </table>

    <h2>Best Practices</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Always validate IDs before saving</li>
        <li>Keep a log of generated IDs</li>
        <li>Use caching for faster ID validation</li>
        <li>Consider implementing a retry mechanism for failed generations</li>
    </ul>

